## ததஅக

[ ākāyaccol ]  
  
பெ. id. +.(dram.) literally  
a speech in the air  
used indramas as a stage direction  
when a characteron the stage puts questions to some one whois not actually present and listens also to animaginary speech  
supposed to be a reply fromthe person so addressed; இல்லாதானொருவனைமுன்னிலைப்படுத்தித் தானேகூறும் பேச்சு. (சிலப். 3  
13  
உரை.)